---
import Layout from '@/components/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'From Dominion to Harmony',
  description:
    'Earthsong\u2019s public framework for stewardship through kinship\u2014principles, practice, and a 12-month plan anyone can adopt.',
};
---

<Layout title={meta.title} description={meta.description} fullWidth>
  <div class="px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-12">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-700 to-teal-800 text-white">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-25 bg-[url('/leaf-texture.jpg')] bg-cover bg-center"></div>
      <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-5xl py-16 md:py-24 px-6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight">From Dominion to Harmony</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-lg md:text-xl text-emerald-50">
          A shared calling: stewardship through kinship. Practical, measurable, and open to all traditions—and none.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a href="#start-here" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium backdrop-blur hover:bg-white/20">Start here</a>
          <a href="#goals" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium backdrop-blur hover:bg-white/20">12-month goals</a>
          <a href="#faq" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-white/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium backdrop-blur hover:bg-white/20">FAQ</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl prose prose-emerald my-12 md:my-16">
      <h2>A shared calling: stewardship through kinship</h2>
      <p>
        Across many traditions, humans are called to care for the world. At Earthsong, we read that calling as a
        <strong>both/and</strong>: our uniquely human moral agency is expressed through reverent kinship with the living
        world. We don't reject people or progress—we align them with reciprocity, responsibility, and repair.
      </p>
      <h3>Why this matters now</h3>
      <p>
        The ecological crisis isn't only technical—it's ethical. When our stories honor the more-than-human world, our
        choices follow: what we build, how we consume, and who thrives from it. "Harmony" is simply ethics in action.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Principles -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-4">
      {[
        { title: 'Reverence', body: 'Treat land, waters, and creatures as worthy of honor, not use alone.' },
        { title: 'Reciprocity', body: 'Take with care, give back with intention.' },
        { title: 'Responsibility', body: 'Match love with measurable action.' },
        { title: 'Repair', body: 'Where harm was done, restore—habitats, soils, and trust.' },
      ].map((c) => (
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="text-emerald-900 font-semibold">{c.title}</h4>
          <p class="mt-2 text-emerald-800/90">{c.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </section>

    <!-- Sidebar note -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl my-12 md:my-16">
      <div class="rounded-xl bg-emerald-50 p-6 md:p-8 border border-emerald-200">
        <h3 class="text-emerald-900 font-semibold">Ancient texts, modern readings</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-emerald-800">
          We draw inspiration from long-standing teachings on caretaking—Sabbath for the land, tending gardens, gleaning,
          mercy for creatures. We make no claim these sources were written as modern policy; we choose to read them
          today as a life-giving ethic for the world we share.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Practice Framework -->
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl my-12 md:my-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-emerald-900">The Practice Framework</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-white p-6">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">1) Worship / Reflection</h4>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-emerald-800/90">
            <li>Seasonal blessings for waters and trees (public, non-sectarian).</li>
            <li>"Sabbath for the Land" pauses in community gardens or parks.</li>
            <li>Gratitude circles that name one local species to learn and protect.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-white p-6">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">2) Learning</h4>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-emerald-800/90">
            <li>Primers on soils, watersheds, native species, and pollution.</li>
            <li>Study groups pairing classic teachings with today's ecology.</li>
            <li>Workshops: "Energy 101" for homes & community buildings.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-white p-6">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">3) Service</h4>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-emerald-800/90">
            <li>River/stream clean-ups; native plantings and pollinator plots.</li>
            <li>Habitat days; invasive removal & trail care.</li>
            <li>Food rescue and gleaning networks to reduce waste.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-white p-6">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">4) Policy & Commons</h4>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc pl-5 text-emerald-800/90">
            <li>Energy audits and retrofit drives for shared buildings.</li>
            <li>Local advocacy for tree canopy, clean water, and transit access.</li>
            <li>Shared purchasing to cut packaging and harmful inputs.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Goals -->
    <section id="goals" class="mx-auto max-w-5xl my-12 md:my-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-emerald-900">12-month interfaith goals</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-4">
        {[
          { num: '10+', label: 'shared service days' },
          { num: '5,000', label: 'native plants established' },
          { num: '1,000', label: 'volunteer hours' },
          { num: '\u221210%', label: 'energy use across buildings' },
        ].map((g) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-white p-6 text-center">
            <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-emerald-900">{g.num}</div>
            <div class="mt-1 text-emerald-800/90">{g.label}</div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Start Here -->
    <section id="start-here" class="mx-auto max-w-5xl my-12 md:my-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-emerald-900">Start here</h2>
      <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-emerald-800/90">
        <li>Host a 60-minute "Harmony Circle" with our free guide.</li>
        <li>Sponsor one native-plant bed or a pollinator patch.</li>
        <li>Adopt a 1-mile waterway with quarterly care.</li>
        <li>Complete a basic energy checklist; pick one retrofit.</li>
        <li>Pledge a reciprocity act: for each new purchase, one repair or reuse.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-emerald-50 p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">How Earthsong helps</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-emerald-800">
          We convene service days, publish simple guides, and keep open metrics so wins spread fast.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section id="faq" class="mx-auto max-w-5xl my-12 md:my-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-emerald-900">Common questions</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
        {[
          { q: 'Is this anti-human?', a: 'No. It dignifies people and place\u2014stewardship through kinship benefits human life, too.' },
          { q: 'Is this political?', a: 'It\u2019s ethical and practical. We welcome anyone who\u2019ll work for clean air, water, soil, and community well-being.' },
          { q: 'Do I need a specific faith?', a: 'No. Earthsong convenes across traditions and welcomes the non-religious. The work is shared.' },
        ].map((i) => (
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-emerald-200 bg-white p-6">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">{i.q}</h4>
            <p class="mt-2 text-emerald-800/90">{i.a}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="mt-8 text-sm text-emerald-700/80">
        This page keeps advanced or esoteric practices private by default. To explore deeper materials, become a member and opt-in.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
